 stochastic pattern and the final state with one long wavelength\nmode, we can observe smaller patches or protrusions of the biggest remaining\npatch in the simulation. Our simulations show these protrusions are few in\nnumbers and will be evolved according to Alan-Cahn mechanism. These protrusions\ncan give an additional effect on CMB which is the existence of aligned\nquadrupole-octopole mode and its direction should be orthogonal to the dipole\ndirection. We conclude that GLTofDE is a fertile framework both theoretically\nand phenomenologically.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Oct 2018 17:55:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2018 08:34:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 12 Jan 2020 13:07:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-14"}
